Serbian Lawmakers Pick Cirovic to Chair Securities Commission

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-07-14T14:13:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/serbian-lawmakers-pick-cirovic-to-chair-securities-commission.html
Serbia’s parliament voted today to
appoint Zoran Cirovic as the head of the country’s Securities
Commission for a five-year term.  Cirovic, up to now a deputy finance minister, will succeed
Milko Stimac, who chaired the five-member commission since 2004.
Stimac will remain on the board.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
